Brazil is a country in which continent?,south America,3,7
Brazil (officially called Federative Republic of Brazil; how to say: ) is a country in South America.
1. He saw it in 1500.
2. Brazilians started moving inland farther than the Treaty of Tordesillas said they could.
3. In 1822, Brazil claimed to be its own country and not a part of Portugal anymore.
4. Since then, the country has become more democratic, but some people feel that there are still big problems in health and education.  Brazil will be hosting the 2016 olympics.

Languages
Most people in Brazil speak Portuguese.
5. That came from German immigrants.
6. Guaraní and Aymará are the first languages of a small number of Brazilians.
7. The country is the fifth largest in the world by area.

